achievements.title: Approximating the present from the past: Stature prediction from femoral length using simple  tools in a Pakistani medical setting
achievements.description: We, a team comprising Aiesha Hamna (06),Amna Ahmed (18),Aliza Altaf (16),Ayesha Hassan (35),Arsala Ghafoor (28),Aima Sajjad (07) embarked on our very first research project as beginners in the field. While the study was simple in scope, it provided us with invaluable learning and hands-on experience that we deeply cherish.

achievements.title: Internship as an First Year Medical Student for early exposure.
achievements.description: I completed a one-month internship during my summer holidays, which gave me valuable exposure to hospital practice. It allowed me to observe and assist in patient care, understand ward routines, and apply my medical knowledge in a real clinical setting. This short but meaningful experience strengthened my confidence, communication, and teamwork skills, while inspiring me to further develop as a future doctor.

achievements.title: Theoretical Foundations of Health Research
achievements.description: Gaining a deeper understanding of the research process was a key part of my academic journey. This logbook details the series of lectures I completed on the theoretical foundations of health research. The course was a fantastic opportunity to learn about research ethics, develop skills in synopsis and manuscript writing, and understand the practical steps of bringing a research project to life.

achievements.title: Developing Professionalism and Leadership Skills
achievements.description: My academic journey has always been about more than just knowledge; it's also about building character. This logbook documents my engagement with the "Professionalism" module, which focused on accountability and professional conduct. The sessions honed my skills and understanding of professional behavior in foundational medical subjects and clinical settings.

achievements.title: Medicose Aids Society's Summer Internship Program
achievements.description: During my summer internship program, I had the opportunity to engage in diverse activities beyond academics. The program emphasized the values of humanity and teamwork, allowing me to collaborate effectively with peers and mentors. I participated in community welfare tasks, including tree plantation drives, which deepened my sense of social responsibility.

achievements.title: Essay Writing
achievements.description: I actively participated in the essay writing competition organized by a student society. This experience allowed me to express my ideas creatively and improve my writing skills. It also enhanced my critical thinking and ability to present arguments effectively. Engaging with peers in such an academic activity built confidence and motivation. Overall, it was a highly beneficial experience that contributed to my personal and professional growth.

achievements.title: Research Orientation Series
achievements.description: Participating in a 3-day research orientation series was a highly enriching experience. The sessions introduced me to the basics of medical research, including study design, data collection, and ethical principles. I learned how to approach research systematically and analyze findings effectively. The program also strengthened my critical thinking and appreciation for evidence-based medicine. Overall, it provided a solid foundation for my future research endeavors.

reflections.title: Learning Holistic Patient Care
reflections.content: Today, I encountered a complex case involving a patient with multiple comorbidities. At first, I felt overwhelmed by the challenge of understanding how the conditions interacted. However, discussing the case with the resident highlighted the importance of adopting a holistic approach to patient care. This experience reinforced that medicine is not only about addressing individual symptoms but about treating the patient as a whole.
